1. Install pipenv (pip install pipenv)
2. Create virtual env ($ pipenv shell, $ pipenv install)
3. Install Django ($ pipenv install django, $ pipenv instal django==4.2.0 - Installing specific version)
4. Create Django project ($ django-admin startproject project_name)
5. Create app ($ python manage.py startapp app_name)
6. Install app to settings.py (Go to settings and add the app name in the INSTALLED_APP list)
7. Migrate database ($ pytho manage.py migrate)
    i. When any models changes or added or deleted, 
       a. $ python manage.py makemigrations
       b. $ python manage.py migrate
8. MySQL database configuration
9. Create superuser ($ python manage.py createsuperuser)
10. Access admin panel
11. Create a View function and url route in the app urls.py (In app urls.py needs to create)
12. Inlcude app's urls.py py into main urls.py (in project folder)
13. Dynamic parameter
14. Create models with all data type and register the model in the admin panel
15. CRUD of models from view function and template
16. Template extends, includes, theme integrations and breakdown, using for loop, if else, data printing in template
17. Login functionality from template and views.py